track_notes:
Mostly unmarked paths (if any) and wide tracks.
--
Parking beside the road near Waldhütte. Follow the tracks until you see the ridge to your left (east). Head straight upwards to the ridge. Then follow the ridge right where the damaged fence is. Because the ridge is also the border to Lower Austria, a lot of Landmarks (stones with numbers) are visible. A small counter-ascent after the wide open area at Haitzmanneck. Following the track to the south is the easiest option until it ends. Then head straight up to the ridge again. Follow the ridge until you reach the summit.
--
Summit has a slightly sloping plateau in Southwest-Northeast direction. Possibility to attach an antenna right at a pole on the summit.

Partially very steep terrain with no path! -- Parking on road near Waldhütte. Follow the street and tracks to the south. At around 980m the track makes a sharp left-turn at a rock. Use this ridge to go up very steep (!!) and without any path (!!) to the next track at about 1200m. From there, follow a small path around the Försterkogel. Go past the small hut to the next track. Follow it to the south until you reach the 180° turn. From there, go up the ridge, cross the big meadow and just follow the ridge to summit Hochdreizipf (1466m) (sometimes no path visible), after a short counter-ascent you reach Lärmerstange (1477m). 
-- 
Summit has a slightly sloping plateau in Southwest-Northeast direction. Possibility to attach an antenna right at a pole on the summit.
